s average can also be written as a\nDunford-Taylor integral. We first analyze the error between this quadrature and\nthe semi-discrete approximation. To develop a fully discrete method, we then\nintroduce sinc quadrature approximations to the Dunford-Taylor integrals for\ncomputing the averages.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 13 Apr 2017 19:01:27 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 26 Jul 2017 18:28:48 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 16 Aug 2017 19:06:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-08-18"}
